              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11460776148663696773">4.5/5 - Irish family saga centering on the friendship of Aisling O&apos;Connor and Elizabeth White, an English evacuee sent to live with Aisling and her family during WWII. The story spans 20+ years as the girls grow up and start their lives in both Ireland and London. <br/>The strange thing about my copy of the book is that it must have been a reprint edition and was 300 pages shorter than the original. Instead of the entire book being re-edited, they took the final couple of chapters and condensed it in</span>
  <span id="freeText11460776148663696773" style="display:none">4.5/5 - Irish family saga centering on the friendship of Aisling O'Connor and Elizabeth White, an English evacuee sent to live with Aisling and her family during WWII. The story spans 20+ years as the girls grow up and start their lives in both Ireland and London. <br />The strange thing about my copy of the book is that it must have been a reprint edition and was 300 pages shorter than the original. Instead of the entire book being re-edited, they took the final couple of chapters and condensed it into 30 pages, making the ending very disjointed and choppy. Disappointing!</span>
