      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heather" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heather" href="/user/show/10738912-heather">Heather</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781787461536" href="/book/show/39092360-light-a-penny-candle">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3250254364" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18413466503095883873">&quot;&apos;Mam, I&apos;m far too old now to be sending silly cards with flowers and horseshoes on them to some woman in England that I can hardly remember.&apos;<br/><br/>&apos;Elizabeth White was reared in this house with you for five years like a sister, and you&apos;ll remember her as long as I say so,&apos; said Eileen sharply.&quot;<br/><br/>Elizabeth White is sent from London, England, to live with her mother&apos;s school friend in Ireland during the Blitz. Elizabeth blossoms with her foster family and becomes especially close with the mother, Eileen,</span>
  <span id="freeText18413466503095883873" style="display:none">"'Mam, I'm far too old now to be sending silly cards with flowers and horseshoes on them to some woman in England that I can hardly remember.'<br /><br />'Elizabeth White was reared in this house with you for five years like a sister, and you'll remember her as long as I say so,' said Eileen sharply."<br /><br />Elizabeth White is sent from London, England, to live with her mother's school friend in Ireland during the Blitz. Elizabeth blossoms with her foster family and becomes especially close with the mother, Eileen, and one of the daughter's, the fiery Aisling O'Connor. Although they have very different personalities, Aisling and Elizabeth become lifelong best friends who will do anything for each other. As I tell my boyz, life is all about the choices you make -- the good, the bad, and everything in between. And boy, do these girls make some choices!<br /><br />This story will give you all the feels 🤣 😲 🤬 😭 🥰</span>
  <a data-text-id="18413466503095883873" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


