  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/360952112" />
    <a title="CB" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10677331-cb"><img alt="CB" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556890513p2/10677331.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/360952112?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="CB" class="user" itemprop="url" name="CB" href="/user/show/10677331-cb">CB</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10677331-cb?shelf=old-favourites">old-favourites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer360952112" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16935995419133927045">I first read this book almost 20 years ago - and loved it then as a teenager. So when I saw a copy in a second hand bookshop for $1 I had to buy it. Often when you return to an old favourite they have somehow shrunk with time but not this. MB is like putting on a comfortable cardie on a cold day and reminds me of hours spent reading in an armchair in our house which was tucked away out of site and where I could lose myself in a book for hours on end. This was one of her first and although her bo</span>
  <span id="freeText16935995419133927045" style="display:none">I first read this book almost 20 years ago - and loved it then as a teenager. So when I saw a copy in a second hand bookshop for $1 I had to buy it. Often when you return to an old favourite they have somehow shrunk with time but not this. MB is like putting on a comfortable cardie on a cold day and reminds me of hours spent reading in an armchair in our house which was tucked away out of site and where I could lose myself in a book for hours on end. This was one of her first and although her books are often derided for being too formulaic - there are times when you need not to think too hard and enjoy the story. For that reason alone she deserves a place in your library as a treasured and reliable friend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16935995419133927045" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
